{"tid":937463,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"澳洲研究：嬰兒缺乏維他命D　或提高患精神分裂風險","createTime":"2018-12-11T14:29:42.000Z","updateTime":"2018-12-11T16:38:52.000Z","uid":212399,"like":1,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":2,"replies":[{"pid":"512bf0cfca9e4431540a1494c62a27319b7e583e","tid":937463,"uid":212399,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-11T14:29:42.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://cdn.hk01.com/di/media/images/2196021/org/16559b7bd94b6e598328161dc8c6cbf4.jpg/xebqVaF7OHmZbD8kC0zcFa9nWBqDeNyRiQnVtokJ1bY?v=w1120r16_9\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.hk01.com%2Fdi%2Fmedia%2Fimages%2F2196021%2Forg%2F16559b7bd94b6e598328161dc8c6cbf4.jpg%2FxebqVaF7OHmZbD8kC0zcFa9nWBqDeNyRiQnVtokJ1bY%3Fv%3Dw1120r16_9&h=1ac2071b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n澳洲昆士蘭大學（University of Queensland）與丹麥奧胡斯大學（Aarhus University）周四（6日）在英國醫學期刊《科學報告》（Scientific Reports）發表一項研究，發現嬰兒缺乏維他命D與成年後患精神分裂息息相關。<br />\n研究人員觀察2602名在1981年至2000年間，於丹麥出世的精神分裂患者，分析他們出生時血液內的維他命D濃度。結果指出，幼年維他命D不足導致後期患精神分裂的風險比正常人高44%。<br />\n澳洲昆士蘭大學教授麥格拉思（McGrath）稱，胎兒發育依賴母親體內的維他命D，因此能補充足夠維他命D的孕婦，或可預防下一代患精神分裂。<br />\n他們之後會開展臨床試驗，觀察維他命D對兒童大腦神經發育的影響，包括自閉、精神分裂等病症的風險。<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.hk01.com/世界說/269809/澳洲研究-嬰兒缺乏維他命d-或提高患精神分裂風險\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hk01.com%2F%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C%E8%AA%AA%2F269809%2F%E6%BE%B3%E6%B4%B2%E7%A0%94%E7%A9%B6-%E5%AC%B0%E5%85%92%E7%BC%BA%E4%B9%8F%E7%B6%AD%E4%BB%96%E5%91%BDd-%E6%88%96%E6%8F%90%E9%AB%98%E6%82%A3%E7%B2%BE%E7%A5%9E%E5%88%86%E8%A3%82%E9%A2%A8%E9%9A%AA&d=Lw1NKwDC7SlkBqgBVo8gCxOFz4pMHIf1Ti9x7C0XgVU%3D&h=4e2a59c9\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.hk01.com/世界說/269809/澳洲研究-嬰兒缺乏維他命d-或提高患精神分裂風險</a>"},{"pid":"4e8678fcc98fca4b07fab93dd29986e13c114399","tid":937463,"uid":212399,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-11T14:30:16.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/bang.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2182c02172fb14e70ea93f5716a5258c2c8c7bf9","tid":937463,"uid":33952,"like":0,"dislike":0,